He admitted possession of cocaine in an earlier interview.
The lawyer was abducted after police found out in their investigation of Scarborough that he had been in regular telephone contact with Ditta in February 2011.
Two investigators followed the suspect and saw him go to Ditta’s house and put the drugs with a purity of 60 percent in a black golf glove under the lawyer’s trash can.
