In the face of changing eating habits, people are getting thicker, but airplane seats have not changed radically.
Between the early 1970s, when the Boeing 747 defined modern long-haul travel, and the end of the century, the weight of the average male American between the ages of 40 and 49 increased by ten percent, according to U.S. Department of Health data.
